                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.641,
                                "byte_start": 85316,
                                "byte_stop": 127948,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 02-299, Entergy Louisiana, Inc. versus Louisiana Public Service Commission will be announced by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.641,
                        "stop": 231.001,
                        "byte_start": 127948,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.641,
                                "stop": 15.748,
                                "byte_start": 127948,
                                "byte_stop": 148323,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on the writ of certiorari to the Supreme Court of Louisiania."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.748,
                                "stop": 24.216,
                                "byte_start": 148323,
                                "byte_stop": 182283,
                                "text": "The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) regulates the sale of electricity at wholesale and interstate commerce."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.216,
                                "stop": 36.401,
                                "byte_start": 182283,
                                "byte_stop": 230975,
                                "text": "Under the filed rate doctrine, FERC approved cost allocations between affiliated energy companies may not be reevaluated by state regulators in setting retail rates."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.401,
                                "stop": 47.833,
                                "byte_start": 230975,
                                "byte_stop": 276741,
                                "text": "Petitioner, Entergy Louisiana, Inc. or ELI is one of the five public utilities owned by Entergy Corporation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.833,
                                "stop": 57.59,
                                "byte_start": 276741,
                                "byte_stop": 315716,
                                "text": "ELI shares capacity with its corporate siblings in other states and this allows each company to access additional capacity when necessary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.59,
                                "stop": 64.962,
                                "byte_start": 315716,
                                "byte_stop": 345182,
                                "text": "Entergy allocates cost for the sharing through a tariff approved by FERC called the system agreement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.962,
                                "stop": 72.046,
                                "byte_start": 345182,
                                "byte_stop": 373603,
                                "text": "Under the agreement, some companies like ELI, make payments to others to cover capacity cost."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.046,
                                "stop": 82.39,
                                "byte_start": 373603,
                                "byte_stop": 414877,
                                "text": "In the 1980\u0027s the operating committe which administers the system agreement initiated the Extended Reserve Shutdown or ERS program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.39,
                                "stop": 94.294,
                                "byte_start": 414877,
                                "byte_stop": 462524,
                                "text": "The ERS program responded to systemwide overcapacity by allowing some generating units not immediately necessary for capacity needs to be effectively mothballed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.294,
                                "stop": 104.908,
                                "byte_start": 462524,
                                "byte_stop": 505052,
                                "text": "Because ERS units could be reactivated if needed, they were considered available for purposes of calculating capacity cost payment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.908,
                                "stop": 119.064,
                                "byte_start": 505052,
                                "byte_stop": 561580,
                                "text": "In August of 1997, FERC found that Entergy had violated the system agreement in classifying ERS units as available but determined that a refund was not due ELI customers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.064,
                                "stop": 135.497,
                                "byte_start": 561580,
                                "byte_stop": 627305,
                                "text": "FERC approved an amendment to the system agreement allowing ERS unit to be treated as available if the operating committee determines that it intends to return the unit to service at a future day."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.497,
                                "stop": 143.93,
                                "byte_start": 627305,
                                "byte_stop": 661055,
                                "text": "In 1997, ELI made its annual retail rate filing with respondent, Louisiana Public Service Commission."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.93,
                                "stop": 153.001,
                                "byte_start": 661055,
                                "byte_stop": 697417,
                                "text": "One of the contested issues in this proceeding was whether the cost of ERS units should be considered in setting ELI\u0027s retail rates."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.001,
                                "stop": 171.336,
                                "byte_start": 697417,
                                "byte_stop": 770665,
                                "text": "In finding its review to the period after the FERC order had issued, the Commission concluded that it was not preempted from disallowing ELI\u0027s payments or capacity, and ELI was not permitted to charge retail rates that reflected the cost of these payments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.336,
                                "stop": 179.555,
                                "byte_start": 770665,
                                "byte_stop": 803579,
                                "text": "The State District Court denied ELI\u0027s petition for review and the State Supreme Court upheld the Commission\u0027s decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.555,
                                "stop": 185.45,
                                "byte_start": 803579,
                                "byte_stop": 827194,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we reverse the Louisiana Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.45,
                                "stop": 201.193,
                                "byte_start": 827194,
                                "byte_stop": 890096,
                                "text": "Under our decisions and Nantahala Power \u0026 Light company versus Thornburg and Mississippi Power \u0026 Light Company versus Mississippi ex rel. Moore, the Commission\u0027s order is preempted through the filed rate doctrine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.193,
                                "stop": 208.988,
                                "byte_start": 890096,
                                "byte_stop": 921339,
                                "text": "In both of these cases, we held that FERC approved cost allocations could not be second guess by state regulators."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.988,
                                "stop": 222.325,
                                "byte_start": 921339,
                                "byte_stop": 974629,
                                "text": "The only differnce between the tariffs in Nantahala and MP\u0026L and the tariff in this case is that this one grants the regulated holding company discretion to set the precise allocation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.325,
                                "stop": 228.197,
                                "byte_start": 974629,
                                "byte_stop": 998139,
                                "text": "We do not find the distinction significant enough to save the Commission\u0027s order from preemption."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.197,
                                "stop": 231.001,
                                "byte_start": 998139,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
